overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of a sleep questionnaire
  application to verify its adherence to the provided Statement of Work and
  detailed questionnaire specification. The review identified several critical
  gaps in the existing implementation. Subsequently, the focus shifted to
  implementing these missing features. Key additions included a 1-10 severity
  scale for tiredness interference, complete with safety warnings for high
  scores, integrated into both the interactive form and the generated PDF
  report. Logic for detecting and reporting Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea
  (COMISA) and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome was also added, providing more
  nuanced diagnostic insights and tailored recommendations. Finally, a dedicated
  "Resources & Next Steps" section with relevant outbound links to professional
  directories and educational materials was incorporated into both the web and
  PDF versions of the report, enhancing the actionable guidance provided to
  users.
